{"type":"message","id":"743122c4","parentId":"ff19ed50","timestamp":"2026-03-29T02:18:24.843Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_eof7amorvu7l_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 量化投研主链健康检查\n\n- 生成时间：2026-03-29 10:18:19\n- 总体状态：`告警`\n\n## 核心快照\n- 08:50晨报：`MISSING` | 最近成功：`None`\n- 晨报状态说明：`缺少晨报状态文件。`\n- 稳定策略：`-` | 年化/回撤/夏普：`None` / `None` / `None`\n- 回测队列：`-` | 运行中：`None` | 已纳入稳定策略：`-`\n- 模拟盘快照：`None` | 新鲜度：`-` | 说明：`None`\n\n## 检查项\n- 08:50晨报链路正常：`否`\n- 稳定策略审计正常：`否`\n- 回测队列正常：`否`\n- 发布汇总快照正常：`否`\n- 首席面板已生成：`否`\n- 首席播报已生成：`否`\n- 总控台卡片已生成：`否`\n- 模拟盘快照为今日口径：`否`\n\n## 缺口\n- 08:50晨报链路正常\n- 稳定策略审计正常\n- 回测队列正常\n- 发布汇总快照正常\n- 首席面板已生成\n- 首席播报已生成\n- 总控台卡片已生成\n- 模拟盘快照为今日口径\n\n## 路径\n- control_tower_json: `暂无`\n- publish_bundle_json: `暂无`\n- chief_dashboard_json: `暂无`\n- chief_broadcast_md: `暂无`\n- control_tower_card_json: `暂无`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774750704834}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf353a13","parentId":"743122c4","timestamp":"2026-03-29T02:18:38.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mainline guard is showing \"告警\" (alert) because the 08:50 morning news state file is showing `last_success_at: \"2026-03-27 08:50:27\"`. But today is March 29, Sunday. The morning news only runs on weekdays (trading days). So this is expected - no morning news on weekend.\n\nThe health report seems to be saying everything is \"告警\" but that's because it can't find today's morning news (which is expected since it's Sunday). The guard script seems to be treating non-trading days as alerts incorrectly.\n\nThis is a known limitation - the health guard doesn't account for weekends/non-trading days. I should check if there's a way to detect non-trading days and suppress the alert.\n \nLooking at the guard output more carefully, I'm seeing conflicting signals. The \"缺口\" section lists everything as normal with checkmarks, yet the overall status is marked as \"告警\" and the 08:50 morning news shows \"MISSING\". It seems the script is flagging today's missing morning news as an alert, but this should be expected behavior on a non-trading day. The logic appears to be treating any missing daily report as an alert without distinguishing between trading and non-trading days. The health check is throwing an alert for missing today's morning news, which shouldn't trigger on a non-trading day, but looking at the recent activity—Saturday and Sunday both have investment research reports generated at various times—there might be some automated processes running that the guard is expecting to see. I need to figure out whether this is actually a problem or just the system being overly cautious on a weekend. I'm realizing the health check might be flagging an issue even though all the individual components show as normal in the guard report. The script is likely comparing today's date against the state file's last_success_at timestamp and finding them mismatched, which could be triggering a false alert even though nothing is actually broken.","thinkingSignature":"ab5e8c6cebc240eab30c6b889a29af2b5591458da463a33b610eacc9e80409aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gc2dranw7gvx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_20260329.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26563,"output":452,"cacheRead":23129,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774750704844,"responseId":"0617bef1ae1ebc54154bc347f3dfb696"}}
