{"type":"message","id":"dd699774","parentId":"735156a3","timestamp":"2026-03-29T02:19:17.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The control tower state file doesn't exist. This is the root cause of the ALERT. Without it, the health check can't get any of the subsystem statuses.\n\nHowever, the key question is: should I try to regenerate it, or is this expected because it's Sunday (non-trading day)?\n\nLooking at the research reports that exist from the past few days, the system was clearly running. The control tower state might not be persisting properly, or it might be generated by a cron job that hasn't run yet today.\n\nLet me check the cron configuration or see if there's a way to regenerate the control tower state.Actually, let me focus on what needs to be done. The heartbeat is showing an ALERT for the quant ops. But today is Sunday, non-trading day. \n\nSince it's a non-trading day, the alert is likely expected. The control tower state file is missing from Sunday, but the underlying research reports from Friday and Saturday are still present, so the system itself isn't broken—it's just that the state aggregation hasn't run yet today. I should note this as a non-critical issue for Sunday and move on to the next check.\n\nNow I'll review the self-improvement findings to send to Feishu. There are 39 learning entries, 31 error entries, and 1 feature request, with 31 high-priority pending items but no auto-promotion candidates or new skill drafts today. I'll compile these into a summary for Feishu.","thinkingSignature":"f0753c8a16e2775723c0cd4bb7f5b82c7f0fb3b72c5d61572113c2ca87ebd546"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gv68wt592kft_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/investment_research_data_source_health_state.json 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in d.items() if k in ['status','date_tag','generated_at','overall_status']}, en